<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>Expand and simplify the expression:</p>
<p><me> (x + {4})(x + {3}) </me></p>
<p>Write your final answer in simplest form possible.</p>
<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
To expand the expression:
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + {4})(x + {3})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Each term in the first bracket must multiply each term in the second bracket.
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Multiply <m>x</m> by both terms in the second bracket.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x(x + {3}) = x^2 + {3}x
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Multiply <m>{4}</m> by both terms in the second bracket.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{4}(x + {3}) = {4}x + {12}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Add the results together.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + {3}x + {4}x + {12}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Collect like terms.
</p>

<p>
<me>
= x^2 + {7}x + {12}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the quadratic expression in simplest form is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + {7}x + {12}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>x^2+7 x+12</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>